name: Rhodomyrtus psidioides (G.Don) Benth.
locality: Immediately upstream of Simpsons Falls, upper Ithaca Creek, Mt Coot-tha.
occurrenceRemarks: Tall shrub to small tree to 3.5m tall. Trunk slender, multi-stemmed at base, pale, bark sub-papery. Leaves dark green, aromatic when crushed. Main vein raised above. Flowers cream, conspicuous.
habitat: Rocky gully line of gravel, sand and rock pavement derived from the Bunya Phyllites. Narrow fringing vegetation of Melaleuca viminalis, Acmena smithii, Glochidion ferdinandi and Acronychia species, with lower shrubs of Ochna serrulata, sparse groundlayer of Lomandra longifolia and Imperata cylindrica. Area subject to recent flash-flooding. Adjacent vegetation is open forest of Lophostemon confertus, Eucalyptus crebra and Eucalyptus major.
